Socket-Based Communication
Sockets se hum ek tarike se 2-way communication karte hai.
Sockets ek endpoint hai jaha se data send aur receive hota hai.
Sockets ek IP address aur port number se identify kiye jaate hai.

Remote Method Invocation (RMI)
If you can make the person on the other end do some work for you it would be great.
RMI ek aisi cheez hai jisse tum dusre bande ke objects ko use kar sakte ho.
You write your own functions and they can be triggered on the device of someone else.

Difference between Socket and RMI
Socket ek low-level communication API hai jabki RMI ek high-level communication API hai.
Socket ek IP address aur port number se identify kiya jaata hai jabki RMI ek remote object reference se identify kiya jaata hai.
Socket ek byte stream provide karta hai jabki RMI ek object stream provide karta hai.

Server Socket
ServerSocket client ke request ko accept karne ke liye use hota hai.

Client Socket
ClientSocket server ke sath communication karne ke liye use hota hai.
ClientSocket server ko data bhejta aur usse data receive karta hai.

Port
Port ek logical connection hai jiska use client aur server ke beech communication ke liye kiya jaata hai.
It is used to listen the request of the clients.
Port number 16-bit unsigned integer hai jiska value 0 se 65565 tak hota hai.

Backlog
Backlog ek queue hai jisme clients wait karte hai.
Backlog ka default value 50 hota hai.

Methods of ServerSocket class
accept() method
accept() method client ke request ko accept karne ke liye use hota hai.
The moment it receives a request from the client, it returns the object of ClientSocket.

stops() method
stops() method server ko request accept karna band karne ke liye use hota hai.


